LayoutNode.Content: I purchased a watch at a steep discount, but I needed to remove some links from it. If I were totake it to a watch repair person that would add to the price of the watch, so I purchased this kit,and I am glad that I did. The instructions were easy to understand. I was able to remove theunwanted links and put the watch back together again. I am now on the outlook for anotherdiscounted watch - and I have my handy watch kit to remove any unwanted links! LayoutNode.Content: For the price, this package can't be beat. Speaking of beating, don't be rough on the items, it'sdefinitely not built for tough like other lifetime tools. But remember, this was made to fixwatches, not steel construction projects. Besides, you want to be gentle with your watchesanyways to avoid scratches and other possible damage. This value package saved me at least1/2 of what they wanted to charge me at the mall to do that same work. Not only that, I used iton a second watch I also have. Nice to know I have the tools for future occasions when a watchneeds battery replacement. Not only for my watches but for family or friends. This is for suremoney, time and gas saver. Worth the space in my tool box. See more

LayoutNode.Content: First off you have to realize that you get 16 tools for $6.99. You get what you pay for. I will notbe using these tools commercially so quality can take a back seat. I purchased this kit becauseI'm could not find anything thin and strong enough to push the pin from a watch band. This kitdid the job. I am glad I purchased the kit because by the time I tried using things to get the pinout, I didn't want my watch band to look like I used a hatched to do the job. I will seldom use thiskit, but when I do I will have the tools to "help" me with the task. See more
